Creating an empathy map for a card game aimed at students around the world learning about NASA and space is a great way to understand their needs and challenges. Here‚Äôs a structured approach to the empathy map, focusing on four key areas: What Students Say, Think, Do, and Feel.
Empathy Map for Space Learning Card Game
1. What Students Say
‚Ä¢	"I want to learn more about astronauts and space missions."
‚Ä¢	"It‚Äôs hard to understand the science without good resources."
‚Ä¢	"I wish I could see videos or have more interactive materials."
‚Ä¢	"Sometimes I don‚Äôt have enough time in class to learn about space."
2. What Students Think
‚Ä¢	"I might not have the same resources as students in wealthier countries."
‚Ä¢	"Learning about space could inspire me to pursue a career in science."
‚Ä¢	"I hope this game can help me learn in a fun way."
‚Ä¢	"I need something that doesn‚Äôt rely too much on technology."
3. What Students Do
‚Ä¢	Participate in class discussions about space when materials are available.
‚Ä¢	Use borrowed books or resources from school libraries to learn more.
‚Ä¢	Engage with hands-on activities or experiments if available.
‚Ä¢	Share knowledge and resources with classmates to enhance learning.
4. What Students Feel
‚Ä¢	Excited: About the possibility of learning more about space and science.
‚Ä¢	Frustrated: By the lack of resources and access to technology.
‚Ä¢	Curious: About space exploration and what‚Äôs out there in the universe.
‚Ä¢	Hopeful: That games and activities can help bridge the gap in their learning.
Additional Considerations
‚Ä¢	Access to Materials: Ensure that the card game is low-tech and easy to distribute, requiring minimal resources to play.
‚Ä¢	Adaptability: Create variations of the game that can be played with different group sizes and in different settings (e.g., large classes or small groups).
‚Ä¢	Community Involvement: Encourage collaboration among students, allowing them to teach each other and share knowledge.
‚Ä¢	Cultural Relevance: Include space stories and examples that resonate with diverse cultures and regions.
This empathy map will help guide the design and development of the card game, ensuring it meets the diverse needs of students while fostering their interest in NASA and space exploration.



