Success (Coin Flip Heads): The Chrysalis Shamans discover dormant microbial life that may have applications in Earth‚Äôs agriculture. They report their findings to GLOBE.gov, receiving valuable data points.
Failure (Coin Flip Tails): The microbes become unstable, and the team must find a way to contain them before they can harm the mission.
Scenario 3: The Pollinator Crisis

Mission Objective: The team has been alerted to a declining population of pollinators in a large meadow. They need to collect data to understand why the pollinators are disappearing.

Choice A: Analyze the Flower Population

Success (Dice Roll ‚â• 4): The Crystal Moths collect samples from the flowers, revealing a reduction in pollen due to environmental pollution. The data is sent to GLOBE.gov for further research.
